Now we need to prove `hm_small : 2 * (b - a) / (↑m : ℝ) < δ`.
We have `hm : m ≥ n` and `hn : n ≥ N`. This implies `↑m ≥ ↑n ≥ ↑N`.
From `hN : 1 / (δ / (2 * (b - a))) < ↑N`, we have `↑N > 1 / (δ / (2 * (b - a)))`.
So `↑m ≥ ↑N > 1 / (δ / (2 * (b - a)))`.
This means `1 / (δ / (2 * (b - a))) < ↑m`.
Since `δ / (2 * (b - a)) > 0`, we can take reciprocals, which reverses the inequality: `δ / (2 * (b - a)) > 1 / ↑m`.
Multiplying both sides by `2 * (b - a)` (which is positive because `b > a`), we get `δ > 2 * (b - a) / ↑m`.
This is exactly what we want.

